==Notable people==
* Charles W. Albertson (b. 1932), Democratic politician who represented the 5th and 10th districts in the North Carolina State Senate from 1993 to 2010. Albertson also served in the North Carolina House of Representatives from 1989 to 1992 and held the position of Democratic Caucus Secretary from 2005 to 2010. He has earned the nickname &quot;The Singing Senator.&quot;
* Grady Mercer (1906–1982). A Democrat, Mercer practiced law and farmed. Mercer became a county judge and, in 1959, a member of the North Carolina State Senate, representing the 9th District. Baptist. Member, Farm Bureau; Woodmen; Freemasons; Order of the Eastern Star; Shriners.

